8:
No wonder. Nao and the others are
a tad later than expected.
12:
She's fine. Besides, this is her sixth
mission.
15:
Remember the fourth one, when
they cut the mission short because
they wanted to go to the beach?
19:
Ah, that one. Sho was practically
jumping out of his seat.
23: Exactly. So I'm not worried about—
32:
Oh my gosh, I am SO sorry, Yumu! I
messed up!
46:
So, during our last mission, we finally
found a world that actually fit our
criteria.
49:
You know how all the worlds we
found were awful? Like how the
atmosphere made you cough up
blood, or you'd forget how to speak
after three days, or time went
backwards...
53:
Yeah. We had a big argument about
the last one. Something about
"preserving youthful complexion," I
think...
57:
But this world was different! And
guess what? There were people who
looked just like humans!
65:
We couldn't understand each other
at first, but we managed to become
friends! Only problem is...
69:
Those, um, wiggly things... Devourers
of Stars. They appeared out of
nowhere...
72:
And according to Denah, apparently
they're in some kinda battle? Like, a
war between gods, or something...
76:
Oh, and Aliksir said that if they make
their way here, the sleeping dragon
might wake up again!
81:
Hey, Sho? I'm feeling a migraine
coming on.
86:
If we sever our connection with it, we
might still have a chance, but...
90:
...that means we'll be leaving those
people to fend for themselves! I
can't—
103:
You want us to put the team back
together, right?
107:
Nephtim is ready. Prepare to "leg it"
to the others?
111: Yes, let's go find the others!
119:
Understood. Call upon the alliance,
and we shall aid you in the coming
battle!
122:
Though, if strength in numbers is not
what you need, perhaps those
present may be of better use?
126:
...Are you sure? You're the princess...
You don't have to be part of this.
130:
I do not mind. Though King I may be,
I am a daughter of burning blood,
first and foremost.
134:
That doesn't exactly make things
better, but... if that's the case, I'll be
coming as well.
137:
I can only win two out of ten fights
against Celtie. Still, I'm sure I can
offer some support.
142:
Seriously? You're already stronger
than I am.
147: Well, in my normal form, at least.
151:
Challua coming, too! Challua
change recently, so Challua make
big help!
155:
Don't worry. She'll be our greatest
asset, I'm sure.
164: Right... In more ways than one!
183:
Then allow me to join you. We finally
managed to resolve the trouble
between the imperial court and the
shogunate, thanks to you.
187:
An opportunity to keep myself
hidden is a welcome one.
191:
Thank you! You don't know how
much it means to have you with us,
Suizen.
195:
Have you spoken with everyone
already?
199:
Well... I still have one more person in
mind, but I don't know if she'd agree
to help...
208:
Dude, seriously?! After that huge,
gory fight you had with her?!
219:
It was crazy. She started attacking
him because of some contract they
had, and Ayumu said... What was it
again?
223:
Something like, "Shut it, you
weak-ass loser," I think.
227:
No, no. I believe it was, "Your reliance
on that power proves that you are
weak!"
233:
H-hey, I didn't say that! At least, that
wasn't EXACTLY what I said... I get
emotional when I transform, okay?!
241:
Um... Taiga showed up with new
powers and, uh... took us both down...
247:
Seriously?! After all that talk?! That's
SO LAME!
Wait, why haven't we asked Taiga to
join us?!
251:
My point is, Shuilong's gotten
stronger. And I'm sure she's
probably off losing her temper
somewhere as we speak...
263:
All right, you scallywags! Nao will cut
a path for us, so we handle the rest!
Am I clear?!
272:
Marina at the helm... Why am I not
surprised?
276:
Hey, Yumu. You know what I'm
thinking?
279:
This is our first time fighting
together, side-by-side. You always
promised we'd go exploring
together.
283:
He's been too busy flippin' omelets
to fight. You sure you haven't gone
soft, Alk?
288: Guess I'll just have to find out!
293:
Let's show them what we're capable
of!
